{
  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1544",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1544: Important priority package update for kernel",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-04-07 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-05-09 23:14:00"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-43278:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndm: clear cloned request bio pointer when last clone bio completes\n\nCVE-2026-43273:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nceph: supply snapshot context in ceph_zero_partial_object()\n\nCVE-2026-43238:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/sched: act_skbedit: fix divide-by-zero in tcf_skbedit_hash()\n\nCVE-2026-43214:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nKVM: x86: Add SRCU protection for reading PDPTRs in __get_sregs2()\n\nCVE-2026-43211:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nPCI: Fix pci_slot_trylock() error handling\n\nCVE-2026-43187:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nxfs: delete attr leaf freemap entries when empty\n\nCVE-2026-43186:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nipv6: ioam: fix heap buffer overflow in __ioam6_fill_trace_data()\n\nCVE-2026-43158:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nxfs: fix freemap adjustments when adding xattrs to leaf blocks\n\nCVE-2026-43152:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: hid-pl: handle probe errors\n\nCVE-2026-43147:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nRevert \"PCI/IOV: Add PCI rescan-remove locking when enabling/disabling SR-IOV\"\n\nCVE-2026-43143:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmfd: core: Add locking around 'mfd_of_node_list'\n\nCVE-2026-43133:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nKVM: nSVM: Always use vmcb01 in VMLOAD/VMSAVE emulation\n\nCVE-2026-43132:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndm-verity: correctly handle dm_bufio_client_create() failure\n\nCVE-2026-43130:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu/vt-d: Flush dev-IOTLB only when PCIe device is accessible in scalable mode\n\nCVE-2026-43128:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nRDMA/umem: Fix double dma_buf_unpin in failure path\n\nCVE-2026-43124:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\npstore: ram_core: fix incorrect success return when vmap() fails\n\nCVE-2026-23243:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nRDMA/umad: Reject negative data_len in ib_umad_write\n\nCVE-2026-23231:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnetfilter: nf_tables: fix use-after-free in nf_tables_addchain()\n\nCVE-2025-71267:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs: ntfs3: fix infinite loop triggered by zero-sized ATTR_LIST\n\nCVE-2025-71266:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs: ntfs3: check return value of indx_find to avoid infinite loop\n\nCVE-2025-71265:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs: ntfs3: fix infinite loop in attr_load_runs_range on inconsistent metadata\n",
